==English==
[[Category:English slang]]

===Pronunciation===
*frăg, /fræɡ/, /<tt>fr{g</tt>/

===Etymology===
Shortened from '''[[fragmentation grenade]]'''

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|frag||g}}

#(''US military slang'') deliberately to kill (a member of one's own unit) with a fragmentation grenade<!-- in their tent. In the Vietnam War, frag commonly meant It was popularised as a gaming term by the [[first-person]] shooter computer games Quake and Unreal Tournament.-->
#to kill (another player) in a [[deathmatch]] computer game.
#:''I fragged him but he fell off the ledge afterwards.''
<!--same as above? #to kill (another player) with a grenade in a deathmatch computer game.-->

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#a successful kill in a deathmatch game
#:''I'd been fighting him for ages, and then you stole my frag!''
<!--same meaning as the singular: #(''in plural''(in plural)'' the number of kills in a deathmatch game
#:''I got 40 frags in the last match.''-->

